Concept,AWS Paradigm,GCP Paradigm (The Shift),Architect's View for AI
Boundary,AWS Account: Hard boundaries. You use AWS Organizations to manage dozens or hundreds of accounts.,"GCP Project: Everything lives in a Project. Projects sit inside Folders, which sit under an Organization.","You will likely isolate your Dev, Stage, and Prod AI environments into separate GCP Projects, rather than entirely separate accounts."
Identity,"IAM Roles & Policies: Highly granular, attached to resources or identities.","IAM (Project-centric): Permissions flow top-down. If you grant an AI agent access at the Folder level, it inherits that access in all Projects below it.",GCP Service Accounts are first-class citizens. Your Agentic workflows will run as Service Accounts to securely call Vertex AI endpoints or read Cloud Storage.

Concept,AWS Paradigm,GCP Paradigm (The Shift),Architect's View for AI
Containers,EKS / ECS: Often requires significant configuration for networking and node management.,GKE (Google Kubernetes Engine): GKE is widely considered the gold standard. GKE Autopilot abstracts away the nodes entirely.,GKE is your workhorse. You will package your Python-based AI agents into containers and let GKE Autopilot handle the scaling. It natively supports GPU provisioning for intense workloads.
Serverless,AWS Lambda: Event-driven functions.,Cloud Run: Serverless containers.,"For lightweight AI tasks (e.g., a webhook that triggers an LLM summarization), Cloud Run is incredible. You provide a container, and GCP scales it to zero when idle, saving massive GPU/CPU costs."

Concept,AWS Paradigm,GCP Paradigm (The Shift),Architect's View for AI
Network,VPC (Regional): Spans multiple AZs within one region.,VPC (Global): A single GCP VPC spans the entire globe. Subnets are regional.,Global VPCs make routing traffic to the nearest/cheapest AI inference endpoints significantly easier without complex peering.
Data Perimeter,VPC Endpoints / PrivateLink: Keeps traffic off the public internet.,VPC Service Controls (VPC-SC): This creates a literal security perimeter around your GCP resources.,"Crucial Skill: You will use VPC-SC to ensure that your enterprise data stored in GCP can only be accessed by approved AI models within your secure perimeter, preventing exfiltration."


Concept,AWS Paradigm,GCP Paradigm (The Shift),Architect's View for AI
Storage,S3,Cloud Storage (GCS),"Used for staging raw documents, PDFs, and training data before it is ingested and chunked for your AI models."
Relational / Vector,RDS (PostgreSQL with pgvector),AlloyDB / Cloud SQL (PostgreSQL),"AlloyDB is GCP's enterprise-grade PostgreSQL. It has native, highly optimized vector search capabilities. This is where you will store the embeddings (mathematical representations of your data) for your RAG architecture."

Concept,AWS Paradigm,GCP Paradigm (The Shift),Architect's View for AI
AI Platform,SageMaker (Custom ML) + Bedrock (Generative AI),Vertex AI: A completely unified platform.,"Vertex AI is the command center. You will use the Vertex AI Model Garden to access Foundation Models (like Gemini), use Vertex AI Vector Search for massive-scale RAG, and rely on its built-in MLOps pipelines to monitor your agents' performance."

Enterprise Cloud Service (Paid),Your Local Enterprise Stack (Free),How We Will Use It
GCP GKE (Kubernetes),Kind (Kubernetes in Docker) or Minikube,You will still write Kubernetes manifests and deploy your AI agents into a real cluster running locally.
GCP AlloyDB / Cloud SQL,PostgreSQL + pgvector via Docker,You will spin up a local containerized Postgres database with the exact same vector search capabilities used in enterprise RAG pipelines.
Vertex AI (LLMs),Ollama,"You will run models like Llama 3 or Mistral directly on your local hardware. Your code will interact with them via API, exactly as it would with Vertex AI."
GCP IAM & Networking,Theoretical / Architecture Diagrams,"We will design the GCP VPCs, subnets, and Service Controls using tools like Draw.io or Excalidraw, and write the Terraform code to provision them (validating the code statically)."


Enterprise Cloud Component,Local Component,Architect's Purpose
GCP Cloud Storage,Local Volume Mount,"Staging ground for raw enterprise documents (PDFs, Markdown, text)."
GCP GKE / Cloud Run,Kubernetes (Kind),The compute layer running your Python application and Agentic orchestration logic (LangChain).
GCP AlloyDB / Vector Search,PostgreSQL + pgvector,The vector database storing the mathematical representations (embeddings) of your enterprise data.
Vertex AI APIs,Ollama,"The local inference engine serving the Large Language Model (e.g., Llama 3) via REST API."

